File: Former eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede was dismissed from her previous position due to allegations of misconduct. DURBAN - Embattled former eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede has been sworn in at the KwaZulu-Natal legislature. Gumede was forced to step down from the mayorship in light of criminal charges for fraud and corruption, which she still faces. READ: Zandile Gumede officially removed as eThekwini mayor She now replaces the late MPL Ricardo Mthembu, who passed away from COVID-19 in June. Gumede is expected back in court next month.